The National Intelligence Service on Friday warned of possible terror attacks in Mombasa county by al Shabaab operatives during the month of Ramadhan.Muslims around the world will fast from Saturday or Sunday, depending on the sighting of the moon, to commemorate the first revelation of the Koran to the Prophet Mohammed At least eight police officers have been killed in less than 48 hours along the Kenya-Somalia border towns of Mandera and Garrisa after their vehicles ran over improvised explosive devices.The NIS warned militants have dispatched fighters in parts of Northeastern and Coast to carry out sting attacks targetting security agents and civilians.&ldquo;We have shared the intelligence report among security agents,&rdquo; a senior National Intelligence Service officer told the Star on Thursday.